			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, my solution is much simpler and it works &quot;out of the box&quot;.  Several of the ones you list force the user to do something extra: mine doesn't.  One of the ones below relies on a database of banned emails or IP's - mine doesn't.  The last one you listed (and many other mod's) require disabling certain form fields during registration: mine doesn't.  
<br />

<br />
It just works.
<br />

<br />
Yes, as someone pointed out, it's possible that bots in the future could get around this.  But the point is that right now they CAN'T!  Bots cannot autoregister their way around this one because of the use of javascript to set a variable of a hidden form field.  
<br />

<br />
And down the road, if bots get around it, we can build soething that would toss a random value into that form field.  
<br />

<br />
This thing works, and I have had zero automatic bot signups in 5 days on 2 forums.
<br />

<br />
Just trying to help the phpBB community....</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by jonahan on Thu Nov 09, 2006 8:43 pm; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
